cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation using deep learning techniques. The focus is on aligning the second-order statistics between the source and target domains, which is a common problem in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
